{"type":"click","text":"W4\n    \n      Mutation testing · \"we broke something in this design · find it\"\n      Given a correct Observer diagram. System silently mutates it — removes unsubscribe(), changes inheritance direction, duplicates a class. \"Find the bug in 90s.\" 10 random mutations possible. Trains the debugging muscle.\n      \n        🔎 MUTANT HUNT · 0:45 remaining\n        \n          Subject+subscribe()+notify()\n          \n            Observer\n            +update()\n            ?\n          \n          ConcreteObs+update()\n        \n        Hint: something is missing from the Observer interface. What would break at runtime if you tried to clean up?\n      \n      Mutation types: removed method, wrong direction, duplicate, wrong cardinality, missing interface, broken constraint.","choice":"w4","id":null,"timestamp":1776672716675}
