{"type":"click","text":"W8\n    \n      Hostile interviewer mode · AI grills you on your design\n      After you design. AI plays a skeptical senior engineer with attitude. 10 minutes of probing. \"Why is Payment a concrete class? Shouldn't it be an interface?\" · \"Your Singleton assumes single-process. Prove it doesn't break in my 8-server cluster.\" · \"You seem tired. Want to simplify?\" Realistic interview stress test.\n      \n        \n          😐\n          \n            Interviewer · minute 7/10\n            \n              \"I'm not convinced. You said 'I'd use Singleton because there's only one parking lot.' But at scale, you'll have multiple garages. How does your design handle that? And don't say 'we'll refactor later.'\"\n            \n          \n        \n      \n      Configurable aggressive level: friendly / standard / hostile / Jeff-Bezos-in-1999.","choice":"w8","id":null,"timestamp":1776672746230}
